WLC_EXEC(3)                                              WLC CORE API FUNCTIONS

NAME

    wlc_exec - exec programs

SYNOPSIS

    void wlc_exec(const char *bin, char *const args[]);

DESCRIPTION

    wlc_exec() will fork and exec a new process defined by bin with the
    arguments args.  The bin argument cannot be NULL.


RETURN VALUE

    None.

NOTES

    wlc_exec() will send stdout and stderr to /dev/null and calls setsid() if
    necessary.  The new process will inherit the environment from the
    compositor.

EXAMPLE

    #include <stdlib.h>
    #include <wlc/wlc.h>

    char *terminal = getenv("TERMINAL");
    wlc_exec(terminal, (char* const*)0);
